Define the “AI Buddy” Boundaries (Critical)

Right now, your AI actively recommends buying/selling stocks. That enters regulated financial advice territory.

Improve by adding:
Clear role definition:
“Educational guidance + decision support,” NOT autonomous advisor
Disclaimers + user acknowledgment
Risk profiling before any recommendations
No guaranteed language (avoid “should buy”)

👉 Upgrade your principle:

“The AI provides probabilistic insights and educational explanations, not financial advice.”

2. Add Risk Profiling & Personalization Layer

Before the AI gives any recommendation, users need a profile.

Add:
Risk tolerance quiz (conservative / moderate / aggressive)
Investment goals (short-term, long-term, retirement, etc.)
Time horizon
Income + savings rate (optional but powerful)

👉 This unlocks:

Smarter recommendations
Better UX
Legal protection
3. Expand Portfolio Management Logic

Right now it's “AI watches market and suggests trades”—too vague.

Define:
Does the app:
Connect to broker accounts (e.g. APIs)?
Or simulate portfolios (paper trading)?
Or track manually?
Add modes:
🟢 Beginner Mode → paper trading + learning
🟡 Intermediate → tracked portfolio
🔴 Advanced → broker integration
4. Clarify “How Recommendations Work”

Users will trust it more if it's explainable.

Add:
Signals used:
Technical indicators (RSI, moving averages)
Fundamentals (earnings, P/E ratio)
News sentiment
Confidence score
Risk level per recommendation

👉 Example upgrade:

“Buy recommendation with 72% confidence based on upward trend + strong earnings report.”

